Rider Breaks are Here!


*We know you care about your riders=E2=80=A6 and we do too!*


Until now, whenever riders needed a break, they had to rely on admins to
log them out, often causing delivery delays and impacting their earnings.


*Not anymore.*


We are finally introducing Rider Breaks!
A feature that allows riders to notify the business when they need a tea or
lunch break. Their order assignments will pause for the duration of the
break and automatically resume once they are back, ensuring a smoother
experience for everyone.

User can set up these breaks while creating the roster from
*Riders > Roster & Attendence > Create Roster*




What=E2=80=99s New


How to Request a Break

Riders can easily request a break directly through the *Executive App* by
navigating to: *Shift Management > Request Break*


Break availability is based on the rider's specific shift timing. Whether
it is a 3-hour or a 12-hour shift, riders can request break durations
in *5-minute
increments*.

We=E2=80=99ve mapped out a few scenarios below so you can see exactly how t=
he break
logic works for your riders.


Different Business, Different Needs

Rider break policies will differ across businesses and can even vary across
different shifts within the same business.

While some shifts may allow for short breaks, longer shifts may permit
longer rest periods, it all depends on the business. Rider breaks can be
set up during roster creation for planned shifts.

Based on these settings, here is how the feature will behave for your
riders:

   -

   *Riders cannot select a break duration* greater than their remaining
   allowed break time.
   -

   *Break options are reduced dynamically* after each break is taken.
   -

   *Once a rider has used all their breaks,* the break option will be
   disabled (breaks are exhausted).
   -

   *Last but not least:* no shifts, no breaks!



Peak Hour Confirgration



   - Businesses can also set up =E2=80=98peak hours=E2=80=99 when order vol=
ume is high and
   customers want shorter delivery times.
   - Riders will not be able to take breaks during this duration.
   - Don=E2=80=99t worry! They will be able to once peak hour is over.

What This Means To YouGemini said

Now that riders have a dedicated option in the app to mark themselves
temporarily unavailable for short breaks (e.g., meals, rest, refuelling).

This will lead to:

   -

   No more order delays or reassignments cause rider is unavailable without
   informing
   -

   Less Manual operational intervention by the admins during rider
   unavailablity
   -

   Positive impact on rider performance metrics (e.g., acceptance rate)
   -

   Accurate rider availability in the allocation system.

Things to note!

Note the following aspects for this release:

   - The feature will be enabled in stages, starting with beta users
   - Even when available, this would still be a completely opt-in feature
   at a shift level
   - System ensures that a break cannot exceed 10% of the shift duration.
   - Break details will be available in the rider performance report for
   better metric tracking
   - The feature will be available only for the captive rider fleet. Riders
   shared with other businesses (Project Dedicated) will not
   have break support as part of this release.

